        faqs: [
            { q: 'Who can apply for GI registration in India?', a: 'Any association of persons, producers\' organization, authority established by law, or body representing the producers of goods in the defined geographical territory can apply. Individual producers cannot file independently.' },
            { q: 'How long does GI registration take in India?', a: 'The process typically takes 12–24 months from filing to registration, depending on the complexity of the application, examiner observations, and any opposition proceedings.' },
            { q: 'What is the validity of a GI registration?', a: 'A GI registration is valid for 10 years from the date of registration and can be renewed indefinitely for successive periods of 10 years each.' },
            { q: 'Can a GI be registered for manufactured goods?', a: 'Yes. GI registration is available for agricultural goods, natural goods, manufactured goods (including handicrafts and industrial products), and foodstuffs, provided they meet the geographical linkage criteria.' },
            { q: 'What is the Statement of Case?', a: 'It is a detailed document submitted with the GI application that describes the product, its unique characteristics, the geographical territory, production methods, and the historical and cultural link between the product and its origin.' },
            { q: 'What is the role of an Authorized User?', a: 'An Authorized User is a producer within the defined geographical area who is registered with the GI Registry to use the GI tag on their products. They must meet the quality and production standards specified in the GI registration.' },
            { q: 'Can a GI registration be opposed?', a: 'Yes. After the application is published in the GI Journal, any person can file an opposition within 3 months (extendable by 1 month) on grounds such as the product not meeting GI criteria.' },
            { q: 'How many GI registrations does India have?', a: 'India has over 450 registered GIs covering a wide range of products including Darjeeling Tea, Basmati Rice, Kanchipuram Silk, Mysore Sandalwood, Alphonso Mango, and many more.' },
            { q: 'Does Your Professional handle the entire GI registration process?', a: 'Yes. We provide end-to-end support from eligibility assessment and Statement of Case drafting to application filing, examination responses, and GI certificate procurement.' },
            { q: 'Can GI registration be obtained for products from any Indian state?', a: 'Yes. Products from any geographical territory within India can be registered as GIs, provided they meet the criteria of having qualities, reputation, or characteristics attributable to that specific origin.' },
        ],
